    <section id="fs-id1169735585040" class="section-summary">
<title>Section Summary</title><list id="fs-id1169737756392"><item id="import-auto-id1169738214644">Young’s double slit experiment gave definitive proof of the wave character of light.</item>
    <item id="import-auto-id1169738249730">An interference pattern is obtained by the superposition of light from two slits.</item>
    <item id="import-auto-id1169738043537">There is constructive interference when <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo fontstyle="italic">d</m:mo><m:mi/><m:mtext>sin</m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mrow><m:mi>θ</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mi fontstyle="italic">mλ</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext>(for</m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mrow><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mn>0,</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mn>1,</m:mn><m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo><m:mn>1,</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mn>2,</m:mn><m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo><m:mn>2,</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mo stretchy="false">…)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>, where <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>d</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> is the distance between the slits, <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>θ</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> is the angle relative to the incident direction, and <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>m</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> is the order of the interference.</item>
    <item id="import-auto-id1169737945882">There is destructive interference when <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo fontstyle="italic">d</m:mo><m:mi/><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext>sin</m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mrow><m:mi>θ</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mfenced open="(" close=")"><m:mrow><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">+</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:mrow></m:mfenced></m:mrow><m:mi>λ</m:mi><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mrow><m:mtext>(for</m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.5em"/><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mn>0,</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mn>1,</m:mn><m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo><m:mn>1,</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mn>2,</m:mn><m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo><m:mn>2,</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mo stretchy="false">…)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>.</item>
    </list></section>

